  "label": "Aurorafall Sleep Alcove",
  "description": "Aurorafall Sleep Alcove is a narrow bedroom partitioned from the habcell’s central aisle by a sliding slagcrete-panel screen and a gasketed threshold lip. A recessed bunk niche is set into the vitrified wall facing, with fold-down storage bays and a restraint rail fixed for use under impact tremors and pressure-lock protocol. The low ceiling carries bundled service conduits and insulated vox cabling, their housings boxed to reduce auroral backwash interference. Armored, washable surfaces and a filtered vent grille keep ash grit from settling into bedding and fixtures.",
